Letâ€™s practice using and creating functions:

Use the mean() function to calculate the average of your lucky_numbers.
Create a function called double_it that takes a number and returns its double.
Use your double_it function on your favorite_number.
Create a function called roll_dice that simulates rolling any number of dice. It should take one argument: the number of dice to roll.
(Optional challenge) Modify your roll_dice function to accept a second argument for the number of sides on each die.



# 1. Calculate mean of lucky_numbers
mean(lucky_numbers)

[1] 7.666667

# 2. Create double_it function
double_it &lt;- function(x) {
  return(x * 2)
}

# 3. Use double_it on favorite_number
double_it(favorite_number)

[1] 14

# 4. Create roll_dice function
roll_dice &lt;- function(num_dice) {
  return(sum(sample(1:6, num_dice, replace = TRUE)))
}

# 5. (Optional) Modified roll_dice function
roll_dice &lt;- function(num_dice, num_sides = 6) {
  return(sum(sample(1:num_sides, num_dice, replace = TRUE)))
}
